Accepting and embracing change can be difficult. Humans crave the comfort that comes with routine and familiarity, especially if we've been living the same way for a very long time. This is especially true for seniors, who may live alone for decades before they decide to move to a retirement community. Even if they crave more social interaction and struggle with daily chores, seniors are often reluctant to move into assisted living. Their fear of the unknown prevents them from seeing all of the wonderful benefits of living in a retirement community. So today, we've compiled a list of these benefits to help show seniors how wonderful assisted living can be if they have a positive attitude and embrace this rewarding change of scenery.
